<subSubSection id="C32A65693C3EA229FF369244FBDDFCAB" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8F36E23C3EA229FF369244FBDDFCAB" blockId="13.[151,1436,518,831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis id="B944EAF03C3EA229FF369244FEB0FD1F" bold="true" box="[199,335,626,651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was previously known from the 
<typeStatus id="548B88403C3EA229FC959245FC6BFD1F" box="[868,916,627,651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">type</typeStatus>
locality, in northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F32776723C3EA229FB459244FAD9FD1F" box="[1204,1318,626,651]" name="Argentina" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, and from specimens collected by Fritz Plaumann in the State of 
<collectingRegion id="49F4F8003C3EA229FD0292A1FC65FD3B" box="[755,922,662,687]" country="Cape Verde" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F32776723C3EA229FBFD92A0FBABFD3B" box="[1036,1108,662,687]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. We add here a new record of the species for the southern part of the State of 
<collectingRegion id="49F4F8003C3EA229FD4E928CFCA5FD47" box="[703,858,698,723]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, with quite higher altitude, a locality that shares a number of elements of the 
<collectingRegion id="49F4F8003C3EA229FE3692E9FD93FD63" box="[455,620,734,759]" country="Cape Verde" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
fauna. The original description and the redescriptions made by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA14B133C3EA229FACD92E8FECEFC8F" author="Vilela" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" refString="Vilela, C. R. &amp; Bachli, G. (1990) Taxonomic studies on Neotropical species of seven genera of Drosophilidae (Diptera). Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 63, 1 - 332." type="journal article" year="1990">Vilela &amp; Bächli (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA14B133C3EA229FE979334FD67FC8F" author="Grimaldi" box="[358,664,770,795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" refString="Grimaldi, D. A. &amp; Nguyen, T. (1999) Monograph on the spittlebug flies, genus Cladochaeta (Diptera: Drosophilidae: Cladochaetini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 241, 1 - 326." type="journal article" year="1999">Grimaldi &amp; Nguyen (1999)</bibRefCitation>
are very complete and well illustrated. We include here photos of the second male ever reported, including the amazing male terminalia of the species.
</paragraph>
